title: Massachusetts - Poverty rate 2000 to 2018
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Percentage of population, containing a total of 19 data points.
Overall Percentage of population has increased over the Year.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2004 and 2005.
The highest Percentage of population, of value 11.9 was reached at Year 2012, and 2013
The lowest Percentage of population, of value 8.7 was reported at Year 2001
